description: Zimbabwe set a new T20I world record by scoring 344 against Gambia in the ICC Men's T20 World Cup Sub-Regional Africa Qualifier. Sikandar Raza led with a stunning unbeaten 133 off 43 balls, including 15 sixes. His performance made him the first Zimbabwean to score a T20I century, cementing his crucial role in the team's success.
title: Zimbabwe rewrite record books with highest T20I score ever

description: A 19-year-old Sikh woman tragically died inside a walk-in oven at a Walmart bakery in Halifax, Canada. Local police are investigating the cause of death, and the store has been closed since the incident. The victim had recently moved to Canada seeking better opportunities.
title: Sikh woman found dead in Walmart bakery oven in Canada

description: Prime Minister Modi welcomed the recent India-China agreement on the Line of Actual Control in Ladakh, emphasizing peace and stability. In discussions with President Xi at the BRICS summit, both leaders highlighted the need for mutual trust, respect, and cooperation to resolve differences and support global stability. This was their first bilateral talk in last five years.
title: What PM Modi told Xi on border issues during bilateral talks

description: Amitabh also expressed that back in the time, there was always the fear of these workers falling and also there were a few incidents including some serious injuries. He added that things have changed now, and crew members have better communication on set because of improvements in technology. “And I notice the workers today and I see all of them in very modern attire
title: Jaya Bachchan's mother Indira Bhaduri passes away in Bhopal

description: Rozlyn Khan criticized Chahat Pandey's behavior in Bigg Boss 18, stating that Chahat is troublesome and demanding at her sister's salon. Rozlyn highlighted Chahat's habit of bargaining and causing issues for the staff, despite trying to appear sweet on camera.
title: Bigg Boss 18: Actress Rozlyn Khan accuses Chahat Pandey of harassing sister

description: American Airlines faces a $50 million fine for failing to properly assist disabled passengers and mishandling over 10,760 wheelchairs from 2019 to 2023. The DOT investigation revealed systemic neglect and injury incidents, prompting unprecedented penalties. Despite recent improvements and compensations, advocacy groups call for more robust measures to protect disabled travelers.
title: American Airlines fined $50 million for mishandling wheelchairs, injuring passengers

description: Vice President Jagdeep Dhankhar warned against the growing trend of Indian students pursuing foreign education, calling it a "disease" that contributes to a "$6 billion forex drain." He criticized the commercialization of education, urging parents and students to reconsider studying abroad. Dhankhar emphasized strengthening Indian institutions, particularly in tier 2 and 3 cities, to curb this trend.
title: Is the study abroad dream a symptom of larger crisis?

description: Pakistan's Punjab province offers PKR 10,000 to 2,200 Sikh and Hindu families for Diwali and Guru Nanak's birth anniversary while making special arrangements for foreign pilgrims celebrating Guru Nanak's 555th birth anniversary, including streamlined visa issuance, top-notch hospitality, and enhanced security measures.
title: Pak to offer cash to Hindu, Sikh families ahead of festivities

description: Israeli forces conducted a missile strike on a Beirut apartment building, captured in real-time by an AP photographer. Despite prior warnings leading to evacuation and no casualties, the attack highlights the ongoing offensive targeting Hezbollah strongholds and financial resources in Lebanon, escalating regional tensions.
title: Watch: Israeli missile destroys Beirut building in seconds

description: Amitabh also expressed that back in the time, there was always the fear of these workers falling and also there were a few incidents including some serious injuries. He added that things have changed now, and crew members have better communication on set because of improvements in technology. “And I notice the workers today and I see all of them in very modern attire
title: Jaya Bachchan's mother Indira Bhaduri passes away in Bhopal

description: Pop star Taylor Swift's relationship with Kansas City Chiefs' Travis Kelce has sparked intense media attention and sparked controversies. The NFL's mishandled references, mixed reactions to a promotional video, and rumors of a predetermined romance plan have kept fans and NFL communities buzzing. Full Scope denies the rumors, planning legal action against fabrications.
title: 3 shocking Taylor Swift and Travis Kelce controversies

description: Astronaut Matthew Dominick shares amusing content from the ISS, showcasing a viral video of him drinking ketchup directly from the bottle. Views on this quirky act vary, with reactions ranging from impressed to grossed out. Dominick's background includes electrical engineering and systems engineering degrees, along with a US Naval Test Pilot School graduation.
title: US astronaut shares ketchup stunt from space while floating; video goes viral

description: TMC MP Kalyan Banerjee was suspended for a day after a violent outburst during a JPC meeting on the Waqf (Amendment) Bill, injuring himself and targeting BJP MP Jagdambika Pal with glass bottle shards. This incident led to sharp criticisms and highlighted ongoing tensions between opposition and ruling party members regarding the controversial Bill.
title: 'Criminal act': BJP slams Kalyan Banerjee for scuffle at Waqf Bill JPC meeting

description: Brett Lee advocates for including Mayank Yadav in the Indian squad for the Australia tour if Mohammed Shami is unavailable. Lee highlights Yadav's impressive pace and the need for a strong bowling lineup to succeed on Australian pitches. He also reflects on India's tactics and recent performance against New Zealand.
title: 'Take Mayank Yadav to Australia if...': Lee

description: Delhi lieutenant governor VK Saxena admitted to the Supreme Court that tree felling in the Ridge area was a mistake and corrective actions are underway. DDA officials misunderstood approval, leading to the error. Saxena assured responsible parties are facing repercussions as internal actions and legal complaints have been initiated.
title: 'A mistake but...': What Delhi LG told SC on illegal felling of trees

description: During the Brics summit in Kazan, Prime Minister Narendra Modi emphasized the importance of uniting against terrorism and reforming global institutions like the UN Security Council. He highlighted the need for dialogue and diplomacy to address global challenges, including wars and economic uncertainty, instead of opting for conflict.
title: No place for double standards on terrorism: PM Modi

description: Former EY employees allege unfair terminations for multitasking during training, citing double standards and a demanding work culture. EY defends the firings as appropriate discipline for policy violations, updating guidelines to ensure presence during educational sessions. No severance was provided to those dismissed.
title: Fired EY employees slam company's 'culture of multitasking' after controversy

description: Netflix co-CEO Ted Sarandos defended changes to the company's culture memo, stating that evolution is crucial as Netflix expands. The revised memo, shaped by employee feedback, now focuses on a 'People Over Process' framework and adds sections on representation and artistic expression while preserving meritocratic principles.
title: 'The culture is changing' — And Netflix's CEO says ‘it needs to’

description: Sitanshu Kotak is set to coach India A for their Australia tour, featuring two First Class matches and a match simulation. The squad, led by Ruturaj Gaikwad, includes top domestic performers like Abhimanyu Easwaran and Sai Sudharsan. The selectors are focusing on left-arm seamers Khaleel Ahmed and Yash Dayal.
title: Kotak likely to be India A coach during tour of Australia

description: Congress MP Manish Tewari expressed satisfaction with the new India-China patrolling agreement along the LAC but called for detailed government reports on the pre-2020 situation and current Chinese transgressions. He questioned India's access to strategic points and requested clarity on Chinese resolutions.
title: 'Serious questions remain': Congress reacts to India-China LAC agreement

description: Rahul Gandhi urged Wayanad's residents to support his sister, Priyanka Gandhi, in her electoral debut. He emphasized their joint commitment to the district, with Priyanka as the official MP and himself as the unofficial MP. Priyanka aims to address Wayanad's issues, promising to invest her energy in its betterment. Voting is set for November 13.
title: 'When my father died ... ': Rahul’s moving appeal for Priyanka in Wayanad

description: India, preparing for the second Test against New Zealand in Pune, faces lineup dilemmas after an eight-wicket defeat in Bengaluru. With Shubman Gill’s return, changes to the batting order are expected. Key players like Rohit Sharma and Virat Kohli aim to regain form. Bowling adjustments include considering Akash Deep to strengthen the attack.
title: India Playing XI: Sarfaraz over Rahul, and is it time to bench Siraj?

description: Pakistani social media star Minahil Malik faces controversy after an alleged explicit video surfaces online. Malik strongly denies its authenticity, calling it fabricated and has filed a legal complaint. This situation has led to significant online bullying and an ongoing FIA investigation.
title: Pakistani TikTok star Minahil Malik's 'obscene video' leaks online

description: Concerns about hygiene on Indian Railways arise as wool blankets are washed monthly, risking allergen and pathogen spread due to infrequent cleaning. Passengers are advised to use provided double sheets or carry personal blankets. Housekeeping staff confirm limited cleaning occurs unless blankets are visibly dirty or smelly, posing health risks, especially for sensitive or immune-compromised individuals.
title: Indian Railways washes blankets monthly: Health risks for train travelers
'Kitab bechne ke chakkar mei ... ': Babita Phogat's dig at Sakshi Malik

description: To bolster passenger safety, 1,200 blade-resistant umbrellas will be placed on 600 trains in Japan's Kansai region. Introduced by JR West after recent knife attacks, these lightweight umbrellas have reinforced components to act as shields. They are practical for use in emergencies, offering protection and allowing passengers to evacuate safely.
title: Japan introduces blade-proof umbrellas on trains to enhance passenger safety
'Wayanad only constituency with two MPs': Rahul on Priyanka poll debut

description: Former Australian cricketer Brett Lee warned the Australian team about the formidable Indian squad ahead of their Test series. Following India's defeat to New Zealand, Lee emphasized India's resilience, cautioning against over-reliance on aggressive play and urging better situational assessment. Before departing for Australia, India will play two more Test matches against New Zealand in Pune and Mumbai.
title: 'India is a powerhouse...': Brett Lee cautions Australia ahead of BGT
'1st time, campaigning for myself': Priyanka makes debut with Wayanad LS bypoll

description: The US embassy in Sri Lanka has issued a warning of a potential attack on the popular surfing spot Arugam Bay, prompting enhanced security for tourists. This follows social media calls to boycott Israeli-owned businesses and protests against Israel. Authorities have set up a hotline and are coordinating efforts to ensure the safety of visitors.
title: US embassy issues travel warning for tourists in Sri Lanka

description: Silver prices have surged, surpassing Rs 1 lakh per kg. The rise is linked to undervaluation and demand from the EV sector. Silver futures on MCX have reached new highs, supported by global trends.
title: Silver better than gold for investment? Prices cross Rs 1 lakh!

description: Kunal Bahl, co-founder of Snapdeal, shares his journey where being rejected by IIT and denied an H-1B visa led him to success. He speaks about these setbacks propelled him towards entrepreneurship in India, founding Snapdeal and Titan Capital.
title: Snapdeal co-founder Kunal Bahl shares how setbacks shaped his journey ahead

description: India's cricket management, including coach Gautam Gambhir, is cautiously planning Jasprit Bumrah's workload due to his back issues. With the Australia tour approaching, decisions on Bumrah's rest and participation are to be made after the second Test against New Zealand, ensuring the fast bowlers' readiness and longevity.
title: Gambhir reveals when India will decide on Bumrah's workload

description: IPL teams are eagerly awaiting the mega auction with franchises eyeing Rishabh Pant, who is likely to leave Delhi Capitals. Discussions hint Pant's desire for captaincy isn't matched by the current management. Teams like RCB and Punjab Kings are particularly interested, making the upcoming auction competitive and pivotal for team compositions.
title: RCB woo Pant as wicketkeeper pads up to enter IPL auction

description: Sunil Tatkare announced the first list of 38 candidates for NCP (Ajit Pawar faction) in Maharashtra. Ajit Pawar will contest against his nephew Yugendra Pawar from the Sharad Pawar faction in Baramati. Ajit regrets fielding his wife Sunetra against Sharad's daughter Supriya Sule.
title: Maharashtra elections: NCP releases 1st list of 38 candidates

description: Somy said, "I don't want Salman's family or friends, Kajol, Tabu, Ajay Devgan, Raveena or Saif to be harmed. We have law and justice, so what is this that Salman should apologize? No one should be murdered. This is wrong. That's why I want Lawrence to talk to me. I will explain to him that this is wrong."
title: Salman Khan, blackbuck and Bishnoi case: What Mika & other artist suggest

description: Ivanka Trump took her daughter Arabella to a Taylor Swift concert in Miami. This was surprising because Taylor Swift endorsed Kamala Harris against Donald Trump. Despite political differences, Ivanka wanted to make sure her daughter's admiration for the singer remained unaffected. A plane with a banner mocking Taylor's political stance also appeared at the event.
title: Ivanka takes daughter to Taylor Swift concert despite Trump's 'hate' for singer

description: Arm Holdings has notified Qualcomm that it will cancel their agreement, preventing Qualcomm from using its chip designs. This comes amid an ongoing legal dispute over Qualcomm’s use of Nuvia's designs without authorization. Qualcomm may face significant revenue impacts or damages if the termination proceeds.
title: Chip giant Arm gives 60-day deadline to Qualcomm: What two cos are fighting

description: Bengaluru's Hennur police made their first arrest in the building collapse case, detaining Mohan Reddy’s son, Bhuvan, for questioning. A contractor, Muniyappa, has also been detained. Authorities are searching for Bhuvan’s father, Muniraja Reddy, and the current contractor, Elumalai. Five deceased and multiple injured people have been identified, with rescue operations still underway.
title: Building collapse in Bengaluru: Owner, his son arrested

description: Microsoft co-founder Bill Gates has privately donated $50 million to support Vice President Kamala Harris's presidential campaign through a nonprofit organization. Gates expressed concerns about a second Trump presidency and highlighted the unprecedented significance of this election for global health and climate change policies.
title: Bill Gates concerned with Trump’s presidency says 'this election is different'

description: The Bombay High Court has suspended the life sentence of gangster Chhota Rajan, granting him bail in connection with the 2001 murder of a hotelier. This significant development comes amid his high-profile criminal history, raising questions about the judicial decisions affecting notorious figures.
title: Bombay HC grants bail to gangster Chhota Rajan in Jaya Shetty murder case

description: Shubman Gill, absent due to neck stiffness in the first Test against New Zealand, is likely to return for the second Test starting Thursday in Pune. Head coach Gautam Gambhir hinted at his inclusion, bolstering India's batting lineup amid their series deficit. Bowling coach Ryan ten Doeschate confirmed Gill's improving fitness, enhancing hopes for India to level the series.
title: Gambhir drops hint on Gill’s availability for IND vs NZ 2nd Test

description: Zomato has temporarily raised its platform fee from Rs 6 to Rs 10 per order during the festive season to cover operational costs and maintain services. This increase follows the introduction of the fee in 2023 and is echoed by rival Swiggy, which also charges a platform fee.
title: Zomato increases platform fee by over 60%, read message to customers

description: The Supreme Court has overturned the NCLAT's decision approving Byju's Rs 158.9 crore settlement with BCCI. It instructed BCCI to deposit the funds with the creditors' committee and ruled that NCLAT's halt on insolvency proceedings was improperly issued without sufficient deliberation.
title: SC reverses NCLAT order approving Byju's Rs 158 cr dues settlement with BCCI
'Toothless' environment laws: SC slams Centre over stubble burning

description: Ahmedabad advocate Morris Christian has been arrested for running a fake arbitration tribunal without a valid law license. The civil court discovered he passed orders to usurp government land worth over Rs 100 crore. Despite previous contempt proceedings, Morris created a fake court setup and continued his fraudulent activities. The court has now ordered an FIR against him.
title: Gujarat lawyer stretches long arm of law, sets up own ‘court’; arrested

description: The Maharashtra State Curriculum Framework for School Education (SCF-SE) now permits students who fail in mathematics and science to enroll in Class 11, provided they score at least 20 marks. The new policy aims to reduce dropout rates by offering students more flexibility and the option to pursue non-science streams. While praised for reducing academic pressure, the policy has raised concerns about lowering educational standards and its impact on students' foundational knowledge in key subjects.
title: Maharashtra to promote students to class 11 despite failing in Math & Science

description: Team India head coach Gautam Gambhir confirmed Rishabh Pant's fitness for the second Test against New Zealand, stating he will keep wickets. Pant had previous knee discomfort but is now ready after managing injuries from a serious car accident. His return boosts India's hopes of leveling the series after their first Test defeat.
title: Gambhir gives key Pant injury update ahead 2nd Test, says he is...

description: Two women in Dubai, lost in the desert, amusingly utilized Uber to find transportation and were surprised to discover a camel as an option. Their unexpected adventure becomes a memorable story as a man named Deepak arrives with the camel to assist them.
title: Tourist 'lost in dessert' orders an Uber camel in Dubai

description: Gautam Gambhir backs KL Rahul to find form in the second Test against New Zealand, dismissing social media criticism. With India trailing the series, the team management focuses on supporting Rahul despite competition and a strong performance from Sarfaraz Khan in the first match.
title: 'Social media doesn't decide...': Gautam Gambhir on KL Rahul criticism

description: In Kanpur, a man named Rahul Kumar falsely claimed he received extortion threats from the Lawrence Bishnoi gang to cover up a dispute with his in-laws. The police discovered the truth, revealing the real source of threats was his wife's family, not the gang.
title: In tiff with in-laws, UP man cooks up ‘Lawrence Bishnoi’ threat

description: The Supreme Court ruled 8:1 that the central government lacks regulatory authority over industrial alcohol production, affirming states' legislative powers. The decision overturns a previous seven-judge bench verdict and follows rigorous legal arguments from both state and central representatives.
title: 'States have regulatory power over industrial alcohol': SC in 8:1 majority verdict

description: A shootout near Culiacan, Sinaloa, killed 19 suspected gang members, with a local cartel leader arrested. Over 30 gunmen attacked soldiers, leading to a deadly exchange. Edwin Antonio 'N', linked to the Sinaloa Cartel, was detained. The incident intensified violence since the arrest of cartel co-founder 'El Mayo' Zambada in July.
title: Mexico shootout: 19 gang members dead in Sinaloa

description: An ad in Delhi Metro by YouWeCan, urging breast cancer awareness with 'Check your Oranges', has sparked criticism for avoiding direct language. Health experts emphasize the importance of early detection and clear communication. Cultural taboos in India hinder timely diagnosis and treatment, necessitating broader education and community support to overcome social stigmas.
title: 'Check your oranges': Ad in Delhi Metro on breast cancer draws flak

description: Two years ago, Virat Kohli's iconic straight drive six off Haris Rauf during the 2022 T20 World Cup India vs Pakistan match was hailed as the 'Shot of the Century' by the ICC. Kohli's unbeaten 83 runs led India to a thrilling four-wicket victory, with his extraordinary shots earning admiration even from Rauf himself.
title: On This Day: Kohli came up with ‘Shot of the Century’

description: Jio Financial Services, controlled by Mukesh Ambani, is in early discussions with Allianz SE to form new insurance partnerships in India, covering general and life insurance. Allianz is considering exiting its current ventures with Bajaj Finserv. This move aligns with Jio's ambitions to expand its financial services, leveraging India's growth potential in the insurance sector.
title: Ambani’s Jio in Talks with Allianz for insurance JVs in India

description: New Zealand police officers celebrated Diwali by performing the traditional Punjabi dance, Bhangra, in their uniforms, delighting the community with lively moves under colorful lights. The viral video showcased cultural exchange and harmony, garnering positive reactions from viewers who praised the openness to embracing different cultures and races.
title: Watch: New Zealand cops show off Bhangra moves in uniform on Auckland streets

description: Former President Barack Obama surprised a Detroit rally by rapping Eminem's *Lose Yourself* while supporting Kamala Harris' campaign. The crowd cheered as Obama humorously noted his nerves and praised Eminem. Eminem also urged voters to turn out. Obama criticized Donald Trump, emphasizing the importance of voter participation in the key battleground state of Michigan.
title: Watch: Obama raps Eminem's 'Lose Yourself' at Detroit rally for Kamala

description: A video shows an Israeli missile striking a Beirut building, which had been evacuated due to an earlier warning from the Israeli military. The attack caused severe destruction but no casualties. AP photographer Bilal Hussein documented the moment, highlighting the power and devastation of the strike. The building, linked to Hezbollah interests, faced initial warning strikes before the main attack.
title: Chilling footage shows exact moment Israeli missile hit building in Beirut

description: In an alarming incident, passengers on the Jharkhand to Goa Weekly Express discovered a live snake in an AC 2-tier coach. The snake was found near the lower berth curtains, causing panic. IRCTC staff and a helpful passenger used a bedsheet to capture it, recalling a similar event last month on the Jabalpur-Mumbai Garib Rath Express.
title: Watch: Live snake creates panic in Jharkhand-Goa train coach

description: Cyclone Dana is intensifying in the Bay of Bengal and is expected to make landfall between Odisha and West Bengal on October 25, bringing wind speeds up to 120 km/h, heavy rainfall, and severe weather. Fishermen are warned, rail services disrupted, and rescue teams deployed in preparation.
title: Cyclone Dana: Trains cancelled, Odisha & Bengal brace for landfall

description: Krushna Abhishek talks about meeting his uncle, Govinda, at home after seven years. He visited to check on him after Govinda was injured when his gun misfired.
title: Krushna Abhishek on visiting Govinda at his residence: Saat saal baad...

description: An E coli outbreak linked to McDonald's Quarter Pounder hamburgers has affected at least 49 people in ten states, resulting in one death and ten hospitalizations. The CDC suspects slivered onions and beef patties as the contamination sources. McDonald's has responded by removing the implicated items from menus in affected states, and the investigation is ongoing.
title: Deadly E coli outbreak linked to McDonald's burger hits US: Key details

description: Former Indian cricketer Shikhar Dhawan shared a humorous video mimicking the viral 'Pankhe Waale Baba' trend, delighting fans on Instagram. The video enhances Dhawan’s reputation as an entertainer. This comes shortly after his August 2024 retirement announcement, marking the end of a stellar 12-year international career, thanked fans for their support.
title: Watch: Dhawan turns 'Baba', stops fan with fingers

description: Salman Khan shot for his cameo as Chulbul Pandey in 'Singham Again' on Tuesday. 'Singham Again' stars Ajay Devgn, Ranveer Singh, Kareena Kapoor Khan, Arjun Kapoor, Deepika Padukone, Tiger Shroff. The film is set for release on Diwali along with 'Bhool Bhulaiyaa 3'.
title: Netizens laud Salman Khan for shooting for 'Singham Again' threats

description: Lucknow Super Giants plan to release KL Rahul for the IPL mega auction due to concerns over his strike rate. Young pacer Mayank Yadav will be one of the top three retained players, joining Nicholas Pooran and Ravi Bishnoi. Meanwhile, several franchises, including LSG and Punjab Kings, are keen on securing Rishabh Pant if he isn't retained by Delhi Capitals.
title: Exclusive: LSG to release KL Rahul ahead of IPL mega auction

description: The state government plans to evacuate up to 10 lakh people from vulnerable districts as cyclonic storm Dana nears. The storm is likely to land in Kendrapada on Thursday night with wind speeds of 100-120 km per hour. Authorities have readied 6,000 cyclone shelters, while evacuation and relief operations are being supervised by senior officials.
title: Cyclone 'Dana': Odisha govt plans to evacuate 10L from vulnerable districts

description: The United States emphasized the necessity of "meaningful accountability" following discussions with India on the assassination attempt on Gurpatwant Singh Pannun. Both nations exchanged information as part of their ongoing investigations. The former Indian official involved no longer holds a government position. Both countries continue their collaborative efforts to ensure accountability.
title: 'Won’t be satisfied until ...': US govt's message to India in Pannun case

description: Union minister L Murugan rebuked Tamil Nadu deputy CM Udhayanidhi Stalin's claims of Hindi imposition, questioning DMK’s stance on Hindi learning. He highlighted PM Modi's efforts to promote Tamil globally and accused the DMK of deceiving the public. Governor RN Ravi faced backlash for omitting a term during a Tamil song at a Hindi Month event.
title: 'Stalin a Tamil name?': Minister slams Udhayanidhi’s Hindi imposition remark

description: Protesters in Bangladesh have besieged the presidential palace, demanding President Mohammed Shahabuddin's resignation. The Anti-discrimination Student Movement led the rally, calling for his removal and a new constitution. The protests, starting in July over job quotas, intensified, leading to Prime Minister Sheikh Hasina's resignation and the establishment of an interim government headed by Nobel Laureate Muhammad Yunus.
title: Tension soars in Bangladesh as protesters siege presidential palace

description: A scuffle disrupted a Diwali celebration at Jamia Millia Islamia campus, leading to police deployment. The situation, captured on social media, was brought under control without major injuries. The cause is unclear, though some reports allege that the scuffle started over a destroyed Rangoli. Police are monitoring the campus.
title: Groups clash at Jamia Millia Islamia during Diwali event, police deployed

description: Delhi's air quality dropped to the 'very poor' category with an AQI of 349. Delhi Environment Minister Gopal Rai has urged neighboring states to halt the entry of diesel buses to help combat rising pollution levels, which pose health risks to residents ahead of winter.
title: Delhi AQI at 349: Air quality plummets to 'very poor' category

description: Indian cricket captain Rohit Sharma had a heartwarming encounter with a fangirl before the second Test against New Zealand in Pune, promising to convey her message to Virat Kohli. Despite Rishabh Pant's knee injury, Team India aims to level the series sans New Zealand's Kane Williamson, sidelined with a groin injury.
title: Watch: 'Kohli ko bolna...' - Rohit caught off-guard in viral video
Shiv Sena announces first list of 45, renominates all its MLAs
Hemant Soren, wife in JMM's first list of 35 candidates
On MP HC's order, accused chants 'Bharat Mata...', salutes Tricolour

description: Babita Phogat revealed her family received only Rs 1 crore from the Rs 2,000 crore earned by the film 'Dangal'. Despite this, she expressed no disheartenment, valuing people's love and respect as taught by her father. 'Dangal' depicts the journey of Mahavir Phogat training his daughters Geeta and Babita in wrestling.
title: 'Dangal made Rs 2,000 cr but my family only got...': Babita Phogat

description: Zepto is bolstering its domestic shareholding by involving notable Indian family offices, including those of Manipal group chief Ranjan Pai and Mankind Pharma brothers. Recently valued at $5 billion, Zepto is also moving its parent company to India, aiming to boost government confidence and align with FDI regulations for a favorable market stance.
title: Two likely reasons why Zepto plans to shift 'holding company' to India

description: Tech Mahindra added 6,653 employees in Q2 FY25, leading among top Indian IT firms with prominent hirings of over 2,000 freshers. Total headcount now stands at 154,273. The company reported a net profit increase of 153.1% year-on-year and revenue growth of 3.5%, surpassing market expectations. Attrition rates slightly rose.
title: This Indian IT company added most employees in second quarter of FY2025
